Definition: Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form "A : B. C : ?". "A : B" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the "A : B" relation.

Positive Examples.explanation: The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A fork can be used to eat. To cook, a pan can be used.
The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A rag can be used to wash. To mop, a mop can be used.
The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A knife can be used to cut. To unlock, a key can be used.

Negative Examples.explanation: The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A knife can be used to cut. To wash, a sink CANNOT be used.
The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A drill can be used to drill. To crack, a shovel CANNOT be used.
The given analogy relates actions to the tools used to perform them. A clamp can be used to clamp. To cook, a broom CANNOT be used.
